<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
 <head>
  <title>CSS Test: running() function combined with display:none</title>
  <link rel="author" title="Mike Bremford" href="http://bfo.com"/>
  <link rel="help" href="https://drafts.csswg.org/css-gcpm/#running-syntax"/>
  <link rel="match" href="reference/running-001-ref.xht"/>
  <meta name="flags" content="paged" />
  <meta name="assert" content="The running() function moves content that is display:none"/>
  <style>
  /* Note: marked as "tentative" because, although running() is intended to act as a way
   * of moving a node subtree in the same way that string-set is intended to copy strings,
   * and string-set works on elements with "display: none", the specification language is
   * "remove elements from the normal flow". Display none elements are not in the normal
   * flow, but then neither are floats.
   */
  @page {
      margin: 72px;
      @top-center {
          content: element(foo, last);
      }
  }
  .set {
      position: running(foo);
      text-align: center;
  }
  </style>
 </head>
 <body>
  <div class="set">This should say pass: FAIL</div>
  <div class="set" style="display:none">This should say pass: PASS</div>
  <p>The above text should be centered in the middle of the page.</p>
 </body>
</html>
